• The ``math-block`` prompt is specialized to write display math blocks. It will default to using TeX unless you specify AsciiMath or MathML.

• The prompt makes use of the document context, including the preceding paragraph, and the math symbols used previously. This means you don't need to repeat youself when writing instructions

• To illustrate, let's [add](type:0) a paragraph, followed by an instruction to create a new equation. Press the $(run) icon to execute the instruction using a LLM.

